      • deljob

        long deljob(String... jobIds)
        Evict (and possibly remove from queue) all the jobs in memeory matching the specified job IDs. Jobs are evicted whatever their state is, since this command is mostly used inside the AOF or for debugging purposes.
        Parameters:
        jobIds - the job Id's
        Returns:
        the number of jobs evicted

      • getjobs

        List<Job<K,V>> getjobs(GetJobArgs getJobArgs,
                       long count,
                       K... queues)
        Get jobs from the specified queue. If there are no jobs in any of the specified queues the command will block until timeout unless GetJobArgs.getNoHang() option is passed.

        When there are jobs in more than one of the queues, the command guarantees to return jobs in the order the queues are specified. If count allows more jobs to be returned, queues are scanned again and again in the same order popping more elements.

        If there are not enough jobs in any of the specified queues the command will return less than count jobs after the timeout.

        Parameters:
        getJobArgs - job arguments
        count - count of jobs to return
        queues - the queue names
        Returns:
        the jobs

      • getjobs

      • getjobs

        List<Job<K,V>> getjobs(long timeout,
                       TimeUnit timeUnit,
                       long count,
                       K... queues)
        Get jobs from the specified queues. If there are no jobs in any of the specified queues the command will block the connection.

        When there are jobs in more than one of the queues, the command guarantees to return jobs in the order the queues are specified. If count allows more jobs to be returned, queues are scanned again and again in the same order popping more elements.

        If there are not enough jobs in any of the specified queues the command will return less than count jobs after the timeout.

        Parameters:
        timeout - timeout to wait
        timeUnit - timeout unit
        count - count of jobs to return
        queues - the queue names
        Returns:
        the jobs
